50:47.336 --> 50:49.463
Kwimper, this is Miss Alisha Claypoole.

50:49.547 --> 50:51.882
She is our State Welfare supervisor.

50:52.007 --> 50:54.552
- Oh, how do, ma'am?
- Oh, stay right where you are.

50:54.677 --> 50:56.512
- You can go now, Arthur.
-But...

50:56.595 --> 50:58.264
Thank you, Arthur.

50:58.389 --> 50:59.557
Hmm.

50:59.682 --> 51:01.642
- What's your first name?
- Toby.

51:01.725 --> 51:02.768
Mine's Alisha.

51:02.852 --> 51:05.604
- Well, how do, Alisha?
- Oh, please relax.

51:06.397 --> 51:09.275
Did you understand what Arthur King
meant when he mentioned your IQ?

51:09.400 --> 51:11.735
I reckon he meant I'm not smart.

51:11.861 --> 51:13.237
I hope he didn't hurt your feelings.

51:13.320 --> 51:14.321
No, ma'am.

51:14.405 --> 51:16.240
There's a couple of things I am smart about,

51:16.365 --> 51:18.868
and one of them's not letting my feelings
get hurt easy.

51:18.951 --> 51:21.245
That's smart. That's even wise.

51:22.913 --> 51:25.457
Anybody ever tell you
you're very handsome?

51:25.583 --> 51:26.959
Only girls.

51:27.585 --> 51:29.170
Don't you like girls?

51:29.545 --> 51:32.965
I like girls all right,
except when they start to bother me.

51:33.424 --> 51:34.758
A young, virile man like you,

51:34.842 --> 51:36.927
I should think you'd love to be bothered.

51:37.052 --> 51:38.512
Well, the bothering part is all right,

51:38.596 --> 51:40.181
but I ain't gonna marry no girl

51:40.264 --> 51:43.392
and build no house
just so I can be bothered regular.

51:44.643 --> 51:47.563
Flight from paternity.
Oedipus is everywhere.

51:48.230 --> 51:49.857
I beg your pardon, ma'am?

51:49.940 --> 51:51.192
Nothing.

51:52.610 --> 51:54.737
You know, Toby,
that the State Welfare Department

51:54.820 --> 51:56.405
is deeply interested in you.

51:56.488 --> 51:57.781
How come?

51:58.282 --> 51:59.950
'Cause you're a very interesting man.

52:00.284 --> 52:01.452
I am?

52:01.785 --> 52:04.747
You have exquisite proportions,
why, your legs are amazing...

52:04.830 --> 52:06.248
That tickles, ma'am. That tickles.

52:06.332 --> 52:08.167
That's because I hit
a very sensitive nerve that...

52:08.292 --> 52:09.960
(CLEARING THROAT)

52:10.336 --> 52:13.339
If you have finished tickling Toby's leg,
I'd like him to do a chore.

52:14.256 --> 52:15.257
Who would this be?

52:15.341 --> 52:16.467
That's Holly.

52:16.592 --> 52:19.595
Hello, Holly.
Say "how do you do" to Alisha.

52:21.096 --> 52:22.348
A member of the Kwimper family?

52:22.431 --> 52:25.059
Oh, Holly's practically a sister to me.

52:25.434 --> 52:26.644
What does practically mean?

52:26.727 --> 52:28.312
We're not related.

52:28.437 --> 52:31.398
Alisha here is a State Welfare supervisor.

52:31.482 --> 52:32.691
That's lucky.

52:33.108 --> 52:36.153
Somebody's welfare
around here needs supervising.

52:36.654 --> 52:38.572
Come and help me fill the water barrel.

52:38.656 --> 52:40.491
I just filled it last night.

52:40.616 --> 52:43.410
Well, it fell over.
I think the twins must have pushed it.

52:43.494 --> 52:46.330
Look, that barrel weighs
200 or 300 pounds, Holly.

52:46.455 --> 52:48.249
The twins couldn't have turned it over.

52:48.332 --> 52:49.750
Maybe they had a little help.

52:49.833 --> 52:52.086
I'll fill it for you later, honey.

52:52.169 --> 52:53.754
Much later.

52:53.837 --> 52:56.715
Right now,
Alisha's got to figure out my welfare.

53:00.970 --> 53:03.847
